posts.name: Alan Tang - Team7587 MutuchenMomentum
posts.cooked: Hello. I just want to clarify one thing: during match does the driver control the start & end of autonomous mode from Driver Station, or FMS completely takes over by first enabling auto mode then enabling teleOp (along with audio cues)? I’d think it’s the latter but just want to confirm. Thanks!

posts.name: Dan Nichols
posts.cooked: It’s all ran by the FMS. When you connect the driver station to the field, the Enable/Disable buttons disappear and are replaced with “FMS Connected”.

posts.name: Tom Winter
posts.cooked: One thing that surprised us our first year was that the during a match your robot will automatically go from autonomous for 15 seconds, to disabled for 1.5 seconds, to teleop for the rest of the match (the disabled part surprised us and required some code re-write).  Use the Practice button to simulate an actual competition.

posts.cooked: Now it just occurred to me that, we actually have some parameters put on SmartDashboard that will be used by the auto code…will we be able to start the driver station, which will popup the dashboard, and enter / adjust the parameters, prior to FMS taking over? Should we connect the Ethernet cable to FMS AFTER we launch the driver station?

posts.name: Tom Winter
posts.cooked: You will connect the Ethernet cable to the FMS before the match starts, and you will have full access to your dashboard so you can enter / adjust your parameters before the students are asked to step back and the match starts.

posts.name: Tom Winter
posts.cooked: And yes, you can have the driver station software and dashboard launched before you arrive, and then connect the ethernet cable when you get there.

posts.name: Mark McLeod
posts.cooked: Get your robot on the field and turned on earliest. Have your Driver Station already on and plug in the Player station Ethernet as soon as possible. You’ll want the Laptop and robot communicating when you go to set your parameters and it has to do that through the field network.

posts.name: Bryan Herbst
posts.cooked:
alantango:

I just want to clarify one thing: during match does the driver control the start & end of autonomous mode from Driver Station, or FMS completely takes over by first enabling auto mode then enabling teleOp (along with audio cues)?

One clarification - FMS controls when autonomous starts and when you transition to teleop, but this signal is still relayed through your driver station. You can’t manually control it, but the message passes through the DS software still. Minor technicality for most teams, but worth noting if you experience issues and are trying to troubleshoot.

posts.name: Ryan Blue
posts.cooked: This. The FMS does not ever communicate directly with the robot. All FMS commands are passed to the DS. Only the DS directly communicates with the roborio
